title: Studio Monkey Shoulder
description: Studio Monkey Shoulder is our new global music initiative, in collaboration with Monkey Shoulder Whisky, dedicated to empowering and celebrating innovative grassroots music communities.

title: Pedro Montenegro
description:
Hello,
My name is Pedro Montenegro and I was asked to write something here to briefly introduce me and the weekly show I host on Worldwide FM, No Problemo.
I was born in Rio de Janeiro and have been living in London for the final days of my hair - at least on my scalp!
For over five years I've been hosting a fortnightly show on Soho Radio called BarKino, trying to focus on the new Brazilian production and the current London scene, but not just that.
And in 2025 I started No Problemo here on Worldwide FM, completely lost and clueless, and looking forward to expanding the horizons of my furry ears.
You can also find some tributes, special shows and Brownswood Basement shows I hosted in this collection.
Hang loose!

title: Worldwide Breakfast: Valentine Comar
description: Every Wednesday from 8–11 AM GMT, kick off your day with Valentine Comar for a musical adventure that spans the globe! She brings fresh new music, exclusive first plays, artist interviews, live recordings, and one hour "Breakfast In…" guest mixes curated by selectors she loves. Each week offers something unique to spark your morning—whether you’re easing into the day or looking for an energy boost, let Valentine guide you through a journey around the world, exploring new sounds, rhythms, and cultures—one breakfast at a time.

title: Peace, Positivity And Blessings: Charlie Dark
WW Rio: Point Of View With Kassin And João
First Thought Best Thought: Tom Skinner
WW Ibiza: Mark Barrott & Pete Gooding
Ear To The Ground: Jay Phelps
KRISP BISCUITS RADIO SHOW: MIKEY D.O.N
James Lavelle Presents: That's How It Is

Classic Album Sundays Exploring Japan with Audio-Technica
New Voices
description: Every month, New Voices unveils fresh music from across the world, featuring an artist who will delve into their record, sound, and inspirations.

title: Rosie Lowe Takeover
description: To celebrate the release of her new album Lover, singer & songwriter Rosie Lowe takes over WWFM w/ guests including Riva Sounds,Live from Can Obert, Harvey Dweller and Tom D Morgan.

title: Jimetta Rose & The Voices of Creation Takeover
Energy Exchange Records Takeover
description: Energy Exchange Records is an independent record label, founded in 2022, operating between Berlin and London

title: Ishmael Ensemble
description: Ishmael Ensemble the celebrated jazz band based in Bristol takes over the WWFM airwaves.

title: First Word Records
description: Founded in 2003 by Aly Gillani and Andy H, First Word Records has grown into a vibrant label, showcasing a rich variety of artists. They bring their diverse line-up to the WWFM takeover series.

title: Love Injection Takeover
description: Love Injection is variously known as a publication, a radio show, a DJ partnership, production duo, and a record label.

title: Time Capsule
description: Time Capsule focuses on unearthing music that captures the spirit and groove of specific moments in history, where the beat is a reflection of cultural consciousness from a unique time and space

title: Tru Thoughts Takeover
description: Tru Thoughts is a British independent record label founded in Brighton in 1999 by Robert Luis and Paul Jonas. The label has put out over 200 LPs of electronic, funk, soul, hip hop, jazz, tropical, grime and other music.

title: Live Sessions
description: Join us as we welcome you into our cozy Brownswood Basement. In this unique and intimate setting, experience performances up close and personal.

title: Rhodes TRIOLOGY Sessions
description:
A brand new collaboration between Gilles Peterson, Rhodes and Worldwide FM.
Gilles Peterson and Worldwide FM are thrilled to announce the first instalment of Triology, an exciting collaboration with Rhodes, focusing on the timeless art of the jazz trio format.

title: Jumbi Takeover
description:
Jumbi Peckham is a dynamic cultural hub located in the heart of Peckham, South London. It is Black owned and aims to platform the African and Caribbean diaspora. Founded on the principles of community, creativity, and collaboration, Jumbi offers a unique space where art, music, and social engagement converge. With a deep commitment to fostering emerging talent and celebrating diverse voices, Jumbi operates as a bar, event space, and cultural venue, hosting everything from exhibitions and live music performances to DJ nights and panel discussions.


Jumbi curates a day of music and conversation for Worldwide FM, featuring a selection of guest hosts.

title: New Soil Takeover
description: Launched in the summer of 2020, the founding principle was to see every artist as unique and then work with each one in a bespoke way to build the foundations for a sustainable career. Since then the label has seen successful releases with Theon Cross, Ill Considered, corto.alto, Balimaya Project and forged partnerships with Church of Sound, Jazz re:Freshed, Total Refreshment Centre, Bridge The Gap, Women in Jazz and Mushroom Half Hour in South Africa.

title: Sello In-Correcto Takeover
description:
Sello In-Correcto is a record label from Bogotá that showcases the sounds of Colombia and the region. The label features a variety of music, including:
Electroacoustic experimentation, Andean acoustic songwriter music, Cumbia, Jazz, Rock, Salsa, and Rap

title: Quincy Jones Tribute
description: Producer, arranger, and composer whose work encompassed virtually all forms of popular music. A titan of the music industry, Jones worked with many of the biggest names in jazz, rock, rhythm and blues, pop, and hip-hop.

title: Future Bounce Takeover
description: Future Bounce is the brainchild of UK Tastemaker Jamz Supernova! What started as a radio show then became a party & now a label. Home to underground talent across a spectrum of sounds!

title: Masisi Radio Takeover
description: A series of takeovers to celebrate the launch of Masisi Radio with Studio Monkey Shoulder

title: Epoka
description: EPOKA is a London based platform that celebrates Latinx DJs and club sounds.

title: Rio 18's Radio Chévere takeover
description:
Birthed in Brazil and cultivated in Cymru, Rio 18 is an international collective formed by songwriter, singer, multi-instrumentalist and producer Carwyn Ellis after his first visit to South America in 2018 as a touring member of Pretenders. This vibrant project has brought together a collection of brilliant personnel as talented as they are varied, coming from Wales, Brazil, Venezuela, the USA, France and England - each of whom being compelling artists in their own right.
After three albums as Carwyn Ellis & Rio 18, all of which bearing their trademark tropical tunes sung in Welsh, with this year’s “Radio Chévere” LP Carwyn stepped back from the mic to focus on showcasing the group’s other members, alongside collaborations with some of the magical friends they’ve made along the way.

https://rio18.bandcamp.com/album/radio-ch-vere

title: Meridian Brothers Takeover
description: Colombian cumbia / Latin fusion / experimental group, led by Eblis Alvarez.

title: Christmas Countdown with Gilles Peterson
description: As we count down to Christmas, WorldwideFM Gilles Peterson will be broadcasting daily throughout December  2024. A jam-packed schedule of exclusive sessions, residency takeovers, breakfast shows, surprise drop-ins, end-of-year roundups, live performances, special guests and maybe even a carol or two.

title: Australia Takeover
description:
Sounds & stories from artists, labels and communities around Australia.

From Perth (Boorloo) to Melbourne(Naarm), Sydney (Eora) to Brisbane (Meanjin) the presenters highlight the flora, fauna and diverse contemporary musical taste from down under

title: Jaubi Takeover
description:
Jaubi is an instrumental quartet from Lahore, Pakistan, known for their unique fusion of North Indian Classical, Spiritual Jazz and hip hop inspired grooves.

This residency celebrates their unique cross-cultural collaborations around the globe. Featuring shows from original Jaubi members in Pakistan and special guests from the full collective around the globe, showcasing Melbourne's jazz and fusion scene to the best music coming out of Poland.

title: First Light: Rohan Rakhit
description:
Join Rohan Rakhit – London-based DJ, actor and co-organiser of South Asian underground collective Daytimers – for a brand new weekly show on Tuesday mornings.

Each week Rohan draws on the eclecticism of the soulful and percussive sound that encapsulates his home city London. From artist, promoter and label deep dives to interviews with those pushing culture in their local music scenes.

title: Wewantsounds Takeover
description: French reissue label Wewantsounds has quickly become one of the foremost curators of global sounds from the ’70s and ’80s on the international music scene. With an eclectic approach, they’ve explored music from Lebanon, Egypt, and Japan, blending jazz, Arabic music, funk, soundtracks, and electro into a rich sonic tapestry. Over the years, they’ve reissued works by artists as diverse as Alice Clark, Ryuichi Sakamoto, Fairuz, Manu Dibango, Freddie Hubbard, and Michel Jonasz—always on the hunt for the next hidden gem to share with listeners worldwide.

title: International Women's Day Celebration 2025
description:
#IWD2025   #AccelerateAction
IWD 2025 campaign theme is 'Accelerate Action'
Collectively, we can Accelerate Action for gender equality.

Step forward in solidarity for International Women's Day (IWD) 2025 on March 8 to help #AccelerateAction. 

At the current rate of progress, it will take until 2158, which is roughly five generations from now, to reach full gender parity, according to data from the World Economic Forum.

Focusing on the need to Accelerate Action emphasizes the importance of taking swift and decisive steps to achieve gender equality. It calls for increased momentum and urgency in addressing the systemic barriers and biases that women face, both in personal and professional spheres.

So, together, let's Accelerate Action to speed up the rate of progress worldwide.

title: Moving Through Music w/ Josh Aitman
Ghana Special
description:
A celebration of the Independence Day of Ghana 2025 curated by Kwashibu Area Band and Soundway Records. 
Celebrating traditional and experimental music and from Ghana, from Highlife and Afro Rock to Jazz, Afrobeats and Afro House. Featuring Okyerema Asante, Strut Records and Klasikbeatz.

title: Raúl Monsalve y los Forajidos Takeover
Heavenly Sweetness
description: Heavenly Sweetness is a French label that was founded in 2007 by Antoine Rajon and Franck Descollonges. Based in Rue des Tamagnards, Villard-de-Lans, France, the label focuses on issuing new releases and reissues with a particular emphasis on spiritual jazz.

title: Andrew Jervis
description:
Andrew Jervis presents a monthly deep dive into new artists and tunes from the Bay Area and around the world, along with musical curios from past eras.

The show will bring together artists for interviews and includes a segment called Curators Corner, highlighting the work of human curators in the age of the algorithm. It's a summit of selection and a gathering around the love of music.

title: LaMunai Records curates (23/05/2025)
description:
LaMunai is a Jakarta-based label and record shop celebrating the full spectrum of Indonesian music—both past and present. From 1950s singer Upit Sarimanah to surf rock band The Panturas. 

For the curated day, they have invited people from their community, including label team Rendi Pratama, Damo from Primasuara and more.

title: Worldwide Festival Sète curates (06/06/2025)
description: Worldwide Festival Sète is based in Sète, the South of France, founded in 2006 by Freshly Cut and Gilles Peterson. The vision was to offer an artistic selection inspired by Peterson's 'Worldwide' radio show. The live performances are set in the open air venue and former fort, Théâtre de la Mer, as well as DJ sets at the beach venue La Ola.

title: Live from KOSMOS Chemnitz (14/06/2025)
description:
Worldwide FM broadcasts live from KOSMOS Chemnitz 2025– a free street festival for democracy in Germany.

Born from a powerful stand against far-right protests in 2018, KOSMOS has grown into a city-wide celebration of solidarity, creativity and civic courage. From live music in laundromats to debates at bus stops and DJs in shopfronts, Chemnitz transforms into a vibrant stage for culture and resistance. 

Catch us live at the Gondelstation stage or listen on worldwidefm.net all day (12:00-23:00 BST) with a full range of sounds featuring sets from our own weekly hosts Valentine Comar and Rohan Rakhit

title: SHUSH curates (04/07/2025)
description: SHUSH is a Berlin-based label, sound system and collective of music lovers & music makers aiming to unite folks through movement & vibration. Their shared goal is to nurture a community that approaches music and club nights without constraints to style, tempo, or form.
